treacy@slipknot.Eng.Sun.COM (John Treacy) writes:

> Getting the delta history and presenting it requires us to read just the
> top of the SCCS file. RCS on the other hand keeps delta comments with
> the deltas, requiring a read of the entire file to display the delta history.

I guess it depends on what model your user interface has of the delta history.
If you start with a user interface that is tuned for SCCS, and port it
to RCS, you will find places where RCS doesn't quite match SCCS and is
therefore less efficient for your interface.

You might try altering the user interface slightly so that it works
quickly with RCS as well.  In RCS's case, for example, you might omit
the delta comments (at the user's option of course), or fetch them in lazily.

